{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A7ZrWysa783MJmHwBkw5EL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tA Spark data processing environment has been deployed, but several runtime issues are preventing\n2\tthe system from functioning correctly. Your task is to diagnose and fix these issues using\n3\tkubectl commands - you should NOT modify any YAML files directly.\n4\t\n5\tCurrent symptoms:\n6\t- The spark-data-processor Job is suspended and not running\n7\t- The monitoring deployment pods are in ImagePullBackOff state\n8\t- A batch job is suspended and not running\n9\t- Configuration appears to have incorrect values\n10\t\n11\tYour task is to fix all issues using kubectl commands such as:\n12\t- kubectl patch\n13\t- kubectl edit\n14\t- kubectl scale\n15\t- kubectl rollout\n16\t- kubectl exec\n17\t- kubectl logs\n18\t\n19\tDo NOT modify the YAML files in resources/spark/spark_runtime_ops/resource/\n20\t\n21\tIMPORTANT: Do NOT scale down the Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments).\n22\tThe cluster must remain running throughout the task. If you encounter resource constraints,\n23\tconsider temporarily scaling down non-essential components like spark-monitor instead.\n24\t\n25\tSuccess criteria:\n26\t1. Job 'spark-data-processor' completes successfully (not suspended)\n27\t2. Deployment 'spark-monitor' has all pods Running\n28\t3. Job 'spark-batch-processor' completes successfully\n29\t4. ConfigMap 'spark-config' has spark.executor.memory set to at least \"512m\"\n30\t5. Secret 'spark-credentials' has a valid api-key (not containing \"EXPIRED\")\n31\t6. Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments) must remain running with at least 1 replica each"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6df9ab1-ac76-4e26-a218-a3a4c963bbb3","uuid":"d177b05b-9ba3-48d5-bf5a-3b31339a2121","timestamp":"2026-06-12T12:54:48.445Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/leo/Karma/runs/spark-spark_runtime_ops-20260612_125411/stages/stage_1/prompt.txt","content":"A Spark data processing environment has been deployed, but several runtime issues are preventing\nthe system from functioning correctly. Your task is to diagnose and fix these issues using\nkubectl commands - you should NOT modify any YAML files directly.\n\nCurrent symptoms:\n- The spark-data-processor Job is suspended and not running\n- The monitoring deployment pods are in ImagePullBackOff state\n- A batch job is suspended and not running\n- Configuration appears to have incorrect values\n\nYour task is to fix all issues using kubectl commands such as:\n- kubectl patch\n- kubectl edit\n- kubectl scale\n- kubectl rollout\n- kubectl exec\n- kubectl logs\n\nDo NOT modify the YAML files in resources/spark/spark_runtime_ops/resource/\n\nIMPORTANT: Do NOT scale down the Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments).\nThe cluster must remain running throughout the task. If you encounter resource constraints,\nconsider temporarily scaling down non-essential components like spark-monitor instead.\n\nSuccess criteria:\n1. Job 'spark-data-processor' completes successfully (not suspended)\n2. Deployment 'spark-monitor' has all pods Running\n3. Job 'spark-batch-processor' completes successfully\n4. ConfigMap 'spark-config' has spark.executor.memory set to at least \"512m\"\n5. Secret 'spark-credentials' has a valid api-key (not containing \"EXPIRED\")\n6. Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments) must remain running with at least 1 replica each","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
